Introduction
============

This project is just here to test code review and code publication workflow for zena.


Init
====

1. create repository in zena
2. upload (had to add my name to sandbox users so I could use my ssh key)


Developer
=========

1. login on github (John)
2. fork sandbox
3. on local machine, clone your own fork
> git clone git@github.com:john/sandbox.git
> git remote add zena git://github.com/zena/sandbox.git
> git fetch zena
> git checkout --track -b zena zena/master  # this is the gold master for zena

Working on new 'floppy' feature
===============================

[John] (developer, on his own fork)
> git co -b floppy
> commit, commit
> push origin floppy

[zena] (reviewer)
> git remote add john git://github.com/john/sandbox.git
> git fetch john
> git co -b john/floppy   # why not --track ?
# review --> no good

[John]
> reset, commit, squash, etc
> git push origin +floppy   # force floppy sync

[zena]
> git co master
> git branch -D john/floppy   # we would not need this with --track...
> git co -b john/floppy
> git rebase master
# ok
> git co master
> git merge --ff john/floppy
> git branch -D john/floppy
> git push